Daily Report on Quality of Air in Key Chinese Cities 
Lanzhou, Xining and Yinchuan in northwestern China suffered slight air
pollution today, while Beijing, Shijiazhuang, Taiyuan, Hohhot, Nantong
and Yantai had extremely slight air pollution.
The report, issued by the China Environmental Monitoring Center, said
that Tianjin, Shenyang, Dalian, Shanghai, Nanjing, Suzhou, Hangzhou,
Guangzhou, Wuhan and 17 other cities enjoyed fairly good air.
Excellent air was reported in Fuzhou, Xiamen, Shenzhen, Zhuhai, Haikou,
Kunming and Lhasa, all in the south and the southwest, it said.
Taiyuan, Beijing, Tianjin, Xi'an, Shanghai and 27 other cities listed
absorbable suspended particles as the major pollutants, while sulfur
dioxide was the major pollutant in Guiyang, Nanning and Chongqing.
The 42 cities include China's four municipalities directly under the
central government, the provincial and regional capitals and 10 key
coastal cities.
